    • Method Detail

      • recreate

        public static UserSession recreate(android.content.Context context,
                                   Clock clock)
        Creates a user session with the same session number and start time, and returns it. If this is the first session being created, it will increment the session and use the current time.
        Parameters:
        context - The app context.
        clock - The clock used to create a start time if required.
        Returns:
        A user session with the same number and start time as the previous session.

      • incrementAndCreate

        public static UserSession incrementAndCreate(android.content.Context context,
                                             Clock clock)
        Creates a user session with the current time as the start time and the previous session number + 1 as the session number. If this is the first session being created, it will increment off the UserSession.SESSION_NUM_BASE_OFFSET.
        Parameters:
        context - The app context.
        clock - The clock used to create a start time.
        Returns:
        A user session with a session number one higher than the previous session number.
